    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Chinese porcelain ware made during the T'ang dynasty (618-907 BCE), including pure white, simple shaped bowls and dishes, and more rarely in elaborately carved vessels.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
